[[Category:Linguistics]]

The production of '''Bhutan wine''' is reported to have first been attempted in the 1990s, with the introduction of an experimental vineyard at Paro ({{convert|2300|m|ft}}) near [[Thimpu]], the capital of [[Bhutan]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=0PHcCQAAQBAJ&q=bhutan#v=onepage&q=bhutan%20taltarni&f=false|title=The Oxford Companion to Wine|last=Robinson|first=Jancis|last2=Harding|first2=Julia|date=2015|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=|isbn=9780198705383|location=|pages=80|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=igZ_BwAAQBAJ&pg=PA76|title=The Dragon's Voice: How Modern Media Found Bhutan|last=Avieson|first=Bunty|date=2015-04-01|publisher=University of Queensland Press|year=|isbn=9780702253577|location=|pages=76|language=en}}</ref> 
[[Australian wine]] company, Taltarni, is believed to have provided technical help, but it is not known whether any wine was successfully produced.

