===Anime===
On July 30, 2009, a retailers' solicitation sheet reported that an anime adaptation had been green-lit.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-07-30/deadman-wonderland-manga-gets-anime-green-lit|title=''Deadman Wonderland'' Manga Gets Anime Green-Lit|publisher=Anime News Network |date=2009-07-30|accessdate=2010-10-20}}</ref> It is animated by [[Manglobe]] and aired in Japan between April 17, 2011, and July 3, 2011. An [[original video animation]] episode was released on October 8, 2011, alongside the eleventh manga volume.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/shop/sp/shop_sp_167.html|title=Deadman Wonderland (11) Original Anime DVD Limited Edition|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Kadokawa.co.jp|language=Japanese|script-title=ja:オンライン ショッピング 通販 &#124; 角川書店・角川グループ|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321190100/http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/shop/sp/shop_sp_167.html|archive-date=21 March 2015|dead-url=yes|accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref> The opening theme is "One Reason" by DWB feat. Fade and the ending theme is "Shiny Shiny" by [[Nirgilis]]. The series is licensed by [[Funimation Entertainment]] and is now available on DVD and Blu-ray.<ref>{{cite web|title=Funimation Adds Deadman Wonderland, Steins;Gate and More|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-07-01/funimation-adds-deadman-wonderland-steins-gate-more|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=2 July 2011}}</ref> The anime was broadcast on the revived [[Toonami]] block from May 26 to August 11, 2012. The anime aired in North America on the [[Funimation Channel]] on November 30, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.funimationchannel.com/schedule/2_e21130.htm |title=Funimation Week 49 of 2012 |last= |first= |date=20 November 2012 |website= |publisher=[[Funimation Entertainment]] |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130124202629/http://www.funimationchannel.com/schedule/2_e21130.htm |archive-date=2013-01-24 |dead-url=yes |accessdate=19 October 2016 |df= }}</ref>

