===Music===
Two pieces of theme music are used for the episodes: one opening theme and one ending theme. The opening theme is One Reason by Deadman Wonder Band (DWB) feat. [[Fade (band)|Fade]]. The ending theme Shiny Shiny by DWB feat. NIRGILIS. The two themes are used in all 13 episodes. Certain characters have their own character song also, Ganta, Shiro, Genkaku and Minatsuki all have their own character song. The songs are created by DWB and NIRGILIS and the characters that the song is for provide the vocals.

===China ban===
On June 12, 2015, the Chinese Ministry of Culture listed ''Deadman Wonderland'' among 38 anime and manga titles banned in [[China]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2015/06/12/china-bans-38-japanese-anime-manga-titles-including-attack-titan |title=China bans 38 anime & manga titles incuding ''Attack on Titan'' |publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service]] |date=2015-06-12 |accessdate=2018-08-31}}</ref>

==Legacy==
Shiro's costume is featured in the video game ''[[Lollipop Chainsaw]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2012/03/06-1/new-japanese-lollipop-chainsaw-costume-dlc-goes-anime |title=New Japanese "Lollipop Chainsaw" Costume DLC Goes Anime  |last=Saabedra |first=Humberto |date=March 6, 2012 |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=July 29, 2015 }}</ref> It can be unlocked during gameplay, by using the coins at the closet menu.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2012/05/10-1/full-north-american-lollipop-chainsaw-outfit-list-revealed |title=Full North American "Lollipop Chainsaw" Outfit List Revealed |last=Luster |first=Joseph |date=May 10, 2012 |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=July 29, 2015 }}</ref>

