{{nihongo|'''''Infini-T Force'''''|インフィニティーフォース|Infinitī Fōsu}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[computer generated imagery|3DCG]] [[anime]] series featuring a crossover between characters from ''[[Science Ninja Team Gatchaman]]'', ''[[Casshan]]'', ''[[Hurricane Polymar]]'' and ''[[Tekkaman: The Space Knight]]'', all series produced by [[Tatsunoko Production]] in the 1970s. The new series is a co-production between Tatsunoko and [[Digital Frontier]] and aired from October 3 to December 26, 2017.

==Plot==
Emi is a seventeen-year-old girl living in [[Shibuya]], [[Tokyo]]. Her father is always away with work and she's grown listless. Suddenly, a twist of fate involving a certain magical item changes everything. A mysterious pencil, of all things, is linked to the appearance of heroes from another world! Could this be the start to the excitement she's so desperately craving, or is there something more?

==Characters==
;{{nihongo|Emi Kaidou|界堂笑}}
:{{voiced by|[[Ai Kayano]]<ref name="Cast">{{cite web|title=Infini-T Force Anime Gets Movie in February 2018|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-08-24/infini-t-force-anime-gets-movie-in-february-2018/.120497|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=August 24, 2017}}</ref>}}
: The main protagonist. Emi is an aloof 17-year-old girl who lives alone in her house since her father has left for unexplained reasons. When meeting the four heroes, she comes across an artifact known as "Case", that has the power of making wishes come true. In her hands, the Case takes the form of a large pencil, reflecting her desire to draw. She is later revealed to be Z's daughter.

;{{nihongo|Ken Washio|鷲尾健|Washio Ken}}
:{{voiced by|[[Tomokazu Seki]]<ref name="G-01">{{cite web |title=Tatsunoko's Infini-T Force Anime Reveals 1st Cast Member, Main Staff |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-01/tatsunoko-infini-t-force-anime-reveals-1st-cast-member-main-staff/.112836|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=March 1, 2017}}</ref>}}
:Twenty four year old Ken is the oldest of the four heroes and acts as their leader. He usually reprimands Emi when she misbehaves and is determined to save her, while restoring the worlds Z destroyed. He has the power of transforming into [[Science Ninja Team Gatchaman|Gatchaman G-01]]. During his first encounter with Z, he manages to make him drop the Case, which ends up in Emi's hands.

;{{nihongo|Takeshi Yoroi|鎧武士}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kenichi Suzumura]]<ref name="Infini-T Force Cast">{{cite web|title=Tatsunoko's Infini-T Force Anime Reveals Main Cast|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-26/tatsunoko-infini-t-force-anime-reveals-main-cast/.113959|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=March 26, 2017}}</ref>}}
:Twenty year old Takeshi is a former agent with the ability to transform himself into [[Hurricane Polymar]] using a special polymer that gives him special powers. After his world is destroyed by Z, he lives for one year as a detective in Shibuya until he meets Emi and the other heroes.

;{{nihongo|Jouji Minami|南城二}}
:{{voiced by|[[Takahiro Sakurai]]<ref name="Infini-T Force Cast"/>}}
:Twenty two year old Jouji is an astronaut looking for a new planet for his people to settle in his original world. He fights as [[Tekkaman: The Space Knight|Tekkaman]] using the "Tekset" armor armed with a double bladed lance.

;{{nihongo|Tetsuya Azuma|東鉄也}}
:{{voiced by|[[Sōma Saitō]]<ref name="Infini-T Force Cast"/>}}
:Seventeen year old Tetsuya is the youngest of the four heroes. In his world, Tetsuya was transfromed into an android called "[[Casshan]]" by his father to fight other androids who threaten human race, after his world is destroyed, he meets the other heroes and Emi, joining them with his pet companion, the robotic dog {{nihongo|Friender|フレンダー|Furendā}}.

;{{nihongo|Z|ゼット}}
:{{voiced by|[[Atsushi Ono]]<ref name="Cast"/>}}
: Emi's father and the main antagonist, {{nihongo|Kazumichi Kaido}} is a man who takes possession of the Case and under the alias of Z, destroys other worlds to fulfill his wish of protecting Emi. His research leads him to discover that in all parallel worlds, Emi is destined to have a tragic death in front of his eyes, so he sealed her in a closed world to protect her. In his hands, the Case takes the form of a small sun, reflecting a memory of his past when he watched the sunset with his daughter.

;{{nihongo|Damian Grey|ダミアン・グレイ}}
:{{voiced by|[[Daisuke Hirakawa]]<ref name="Cast"/>}}
: Damian Grey is a mysterious, flamboyant man who approaches Takeshi and hires his services to track down the Case. He then reveals himself the be a dangerous monster who intends to take the Case for himself in order to become the perfect evil.

;{{nihongo|Belle Lynn|ベル・リン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kana Hanazawa]]<ref name="Cast"/>}}
: A woman from a dying race of inhumans who seeks strong genes to revive her people. She joins forces with Z, intending to take his genes, until she discovers that he is not human anymore, and attacks Emi instead.

;{{nihongo|Raja Kaan|ラジャ・カーン}}
:{{voiced by|[[Hiroki Yasumoto]]<ref name="Cast"/>}}

==Media==

===Anime===
The anime was announced on March 26, 2016. It was inspired by the manga of the same name, but follows an original story.<ref name="Infini-T">{{cite web|title=Infini-T Force Manga Gets 'Full 3DCG' Anime|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-03-26/infini-t-force-manga-gets-full-3dcg-anime/.100286|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=December 6, 2017}}</ref> Kiyotaka Suzuki directed the series, while Toshiya Ono supervised scripts. [[Oh! great]] designed the original character concepts, Koji Nakakita handled the suit and mechanical designs, and [[Keiichi Sato]] designed the original hero concepts.<ref name="G-01"/> The anime aired as part of [[Nippon Television|NTV]]'s AnichU one-hour programming block.<ref name="Infini-T Force Cast"/> The opening theme is "To be continued ... " performed by [[Flumpool]] and the ending theme is "Tick-Tock" performed by Edda.<ref>{{cite web|title=Infini-T Force Hero Anime's Promo Video Reveals flumpool Theme Song|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-06/infini-t-force-hero-anime-promo-video-reveals-flumpool-theme-song/.120997|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=September 6, 2017}}</ref> [[Viz Media]] announced during [[Anime Weekend Atlanta]] that they have licensed both the anime series and the film.<ref>{{cite web|title=Viz Media Licenses Infini-T Force TV Anime, Film|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-29/viz-media-licenses-infini-t-force-tv-anime-film/.122068|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=September 6, 2017}}</ref> It is being streamed on [[Tubi TV]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Tubi TV to Simulcast Infini-T Force Anime|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-10-03/tubi-tv-to-simulcast-infini-t-force-anime/.122173|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=December 6, 2017|date=October 3, 2017}}</ref>
