{{Orphan|date=November 2011}}
{{Infobox company | name = TLS Talent Agency | logo = [[File:New_TLS_logo.jpg]] | type = [[Private company|Private]] | foundation = 2009 | location = [[Raleigh, NC]] |industry = [[:Category:Talent and literary agencies|Talent and Literary Agencies]] | homepage = [http://www.tlsagency.net Official Website] }}
'''TLS Talent Agency''' is a full-service entertainment agency that provides representation for clients in motion pictures, television, branded entertainment and new media.
==History==
TLS Talent Agency is a talent and literary agency formed in 2009. The agency only started with two clients but by 2010 the agency grew with the signing of Business Mogul and TV personality Daymond John, American Idol/Grammy Award winner Fantasia Barrino and TV personality Fonzworth Bentley. The website states they provide representation for clients in motion pictures, television, sports, literary rights, theatre, new media, stand-up comedy, commercials and personal appearances.
==Notable Clients== TLS clients include Grammy Award Winner [[Fantasia Barrino]], [[Daymond John]], Academy Award nominee film director [[James Fargo]], actress [[April Parker Jones]], [[New Boyz]], [[Sway Calloway]], [[Big Tigger]], [[Kid N Play]] and [[Fonzworth Bentley]];<ref name="The Herald-Sun">{{cite news|last = McCann|first = John|title=Bull City connections pay dividends|work=[[The Herald-Sun]]|publisher=[[The Herald-Sun]]|date= 2011-03-05| url = http://hs2.uber.mbin.net/printer_friendly/12175022|accessdate = 2011-03-08}}</ref>
